	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Using S-Video or better interconnects between the PC and the video monitor/TV, then the image should be 99% accurate to a real NES - the only visual difference will be that the PC outputs an interlaced signal while the real NES is noninterlaced. I don't know of any way to force a TV-out to skip the extra half-scanline that triggers sets to interlace, so that sounds like the best one could get.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


