		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />AdvanceMAME is able to mess with your video card registers to output a 15.75Khz signal. I run the DOS version on a MAME cabinet I have, and hacked a TV for RGB input.
<br />
<br />Original I used an AD723 to get S-Video/Composite NTSC for use on a regular TV.
<br />
<br />It works quite well, and you can get non-interlaced output out of a PC. I think windows/dos/linux ports exist.

		

